Heavy Duty Motorcycle Tours

If you're looking for an amazing travel experience, for the best value,
without doing any of the planning yourself, have a look at Heavy Duty Tours.
Since 2003, HEAVY DUTY has grown to be one of Australia's leading motorcycle
tour companies. As passionate travellers they have all the info you need, and
can advise on flights, travel insurance, local knowledge and more.

Beker's Motorcycle Tours NZ Ltd

Although it all started in New Zealand for Beker’s Motorcycle Tours NZ Ltd,
these days they also operate tours in the USA, central Europe and Greece. They
were the first Harley-Davidson Authorized Motorcycle Tour Company in Asia-
Pacific and subsequently have earned an enviable reputation within New
Zealand’s tourism industry.

Hadrian V Twin

With more than a million miles of motorcycling smiles and 20 years of touring
experiences, booking bike rentals around the globe. Hadrian V Twin is your
one-stop shop for all touring needs. Exclusively H-D Authorized for the UK and
Ireland – providing unique tours to Thunder in the Glens, Scotland and Ireland
Bikefest Killarney – we pride ourselves on our personal service, with real
motorcycle people to take your enquiries. H.O.G. members receive 10% off H-D
Authorized UK and Ireland tours.

West Forever

Started by two friends with a shared passion for touring on motorcycles,
_West Forever_  now operates in The United States, Canada, Europe, South
Africa, Chile, Argentina, Thailand, Japan and Australia. Their guides are
multi-lingual and huge Harley-Davidson enthusiasts. West Forever’s philosophy
is very simple: provide any biker from any country with a high quality of
service whatever his destination is.

H-D Adventure Centre

Are you ready for your adventure? You’ll take on some of the toughest terrain
Wales can throw at you in an idyllic setting. The H-D Adventure Centre is set
in 1,500 acres of private woodland with some fantastic trails and spectacular
views. You’ll truly be in the wild as you master gravel paths, stony trails
and Welsh woodland. You’ll learn at your own pace and soon be blasting across
tracks and mastering jumps like a true Dakar racer – even if you’ve never been
off-road before. All riders must hold a full motorcycle licence and be able to
reach the floor comfortably from the seat of the Pan America™ 1250 Special.
All weathers, all terrain, all skill levels. All Harley-Davidson.

Beker's Motorcycle Tours NZ Ltd

Although it all started in New Zealand for Beker’s Motorcycle Tours NZ Ltd,
these days they also operate tours in the USA, central Europe and Greece. They
were the first Harley-Davidson Authorized Motorcycle Tour Company in Asia-
Pacific and subsequently have earned an enviable reputation within New
Zealand’s tourism industry.

Brettours

The original pioneer of European Tours for HOG, Ron Brett has over 20 years
and over 200,000 miles of touring experience.  Ron’s knowledge of riding the
finest back roads is un-surpassed. Tour accommodation is always of superior
standard and never less than 3 stars. All tours are fully hosted and supported
throughout from beginning to end.

Crossroads Motortours

Founded in 2002 in the Netherlands, riding motorcycles and giving customers a
fantastic holiday is their passion, that and riding the finest roads in the
most beautiful locations. Special is the keyword that runs throughout their
tours which run through USA, Europe and South Africa.

Edelweiss

Providing experiences on motorcycles is something of a speciality for this
globally established company. In fact, over the last 35 years, Werner and
Coral Wachter have organised 2,200 tours over five continents, helping more
than 36,000 riders live out their dreams.

Hadrian V Twin

With more than a million miles of motorcycling smiles and 20 years of touring
experiences, booking bike rentals around the globe. Hadrian V Twin is your
one-stop shop for all touring needs. Exclusively H-D Authorized for the UK and
Ireland – providing unique tours to Thunder in the Glens, Scotland and Ireland
Bikefest Killarney – we pride ourselves on our personal service, with real
motorcycle people to take your enquiries. H.O.G. members receive 10% off H-D
Authorized UK and Ireland tours.

HT Moto Turismo

This Brazilian tour company was the first official partner of Harley-Davidson
in South America. They have found and created over 45 different routes in
motorcycle hotspots around the globe, including: the Alps, Canada, California
and Alaska.

Moor Motor

This Dutch company specialises in self-guided European tours. With hotels
booked and routes planned they take the hassle out of touring, allowing you to
explore some of  Europe’s wonderful sights, riding magnificent roads on your
Harley-Davidson motorcycle.

Saddletramp Adventure Travel

Richie Finney has been a member of HOG, the official riding club for Harley-
Davidson owners for over 25 years He runs  _Saddle Tramp Adventure Travel Ltd_
, and as such has led Motorcycle tours all over the world, from the dirt
tracks of Cambodia, through the Himalayas, the foothills of the Western Ghats
in India, the garden route in South Africa, to the whole length of Norway.

Tour 1

Tour1 runs guided Harley-Davidson tours in Europe, and prides itself on
